=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Which cloak would you wear?</span><hr size=1> Gotta say the Cloak of Truth. 5% Med bonus i HUGE for Paladins as it CAN take us over our class cap.<br><br>if you have a 225 Med then a 5% bonus takes you up to 236. Those 11 extra points are nice. <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105286">Gilfalas Elaandrin</a>, Lvl 59 Knight of Tunare & Defender of Nature<br>Bertoxxulous Server<br><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath">Paladins Of Norrath</a> Messageboard Admin<br>Member of <a href="http://www.fedupnow.com/">Dragon Council</a><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usenchy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senchy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 327<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/28/02 8:57:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=326.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Which cloak would you wear?</span><hr size=1> Up to 50-55 I would wear the cloak of truth. Up to that level you maximum HPs are not that important. You do not fight aoe dragons often and CH is not your primary way of getting healed. Also your meditate skill is not maxxed so the +5% to meditation will help reduce downtime. At that level also your AC typically needs a lot of work so the added AC is helpful. You will not fight most times with focus so dex for ion and str makes a little difference.<br><br>Once you go fight dragons with aoe a lot or get almost exclusively healed with CH, then I would switch to the bear cloak.  <p>Senchy Solariatus60 Crusader of Rodcet Nife55 Chanter of Rodcet Nife (Tymbor)Dol Amroth<BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=79641>My Profile</a><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr b